Mr.
Elton
must
smile
less,
and
Mr.
John
Knightley
more,
to
fit
them
for
the
place.
Emma
only
might
be
as
nature
prompted,
and
shew
herself
just
as
happy
as
she
was.
To
her
it
was
real
enjoyment
to
be
with
the
Westons.
Mr.
Weston
was
a
great
favourite,
and
there
was
not
a
creature
in
the
world
to
whom
she
spoke
with
such
